alt_text: adidas - Your Future Is Not Mine
title: adidas - Your Future Is Not Mine (2016)
description: The 2016 Adidas commercial "Your Future is Not Mine," directed by Terence Neale, features influential creatives like Aleali May, Luka Sabbat, and Iman Shumpert, among others, who march confidently towards an optimistic future, challenging the preconceived notions of a dystopian tomorrow. This campaign, produced by the advertising agency Johannes Leonardo, emphasizes individual empowerment and the message that one's future is theirs to create, rallying viewers to defy negative expectations and shape their own destinies through creativity and personal initiative.
director: Exile Edit, Nate Gross, Shane Reid

21 Savage - redrum (2024)
description: The music video for "Redrum" by 21 Savage, featured on his album "American Dream," is directed by Danny Seth and showcases a return to the artist's roots in London. It contrasts iconic landmarks with the grittier areas of Brixton, symbolizing the song's themes. The track itself, produced by London on da Track, samples "Serenata do Adeus" and incorporates elements from "The Shining," including the famous line "Here's Johnny!" Despite some opinions that the video could have more directly referenced "The Shining's" iconic scenes, it has been well-received for its artistic representation and Savage's performance.

title: Blood Simple (1984)
description: 1984 cult-classic movie directed by the Coen Brothers. In it, the owner of a seedy small-town Texas bar discovers that one of his employees is having an affair with his wife. A chaotic chain of misunderstandings, lies, and mischief ensues after he devises a plot to have them murdered. You're seeing a locked-off ground-level shot. We say locked-off when the camera doesn't move. In this case, the character walks into frame and back out. A ground-level shot doesn't always signify the camera is literally on or near the ground, but that the camera on the lowest surface in the scene — in this case the bar counter.

title: Flume feat. MAY-A - Say Nothing (2022)
description: The music video for "Say Nothing" by Flume featuring MAY-A, directed by Michael Hili, offers a visually captivating and surreal experience. It includes psychedelic visuals, with Flume donning a bleach-blonde hairstyle and posing on motorcycles, while MAY-A is seen submerged in black sand. The video uses stark contrasts and vibrant colors to complement the song's themes of post-relationship clarity and emotional expression. This trippy and avant-garde style enhances the song's narrative, making it a standout piece in Flume's discography.

title: Majimbo - Aiza (2023)
description: The music video for Aiza’s "Majimbo" showcases vibrant, energetic scenes that match the feel-good thumpy pop bassline and braggadocious flow of the song. Aiza, full of confidence, is seen walking down colorful city streets that transform into impromptu fashion runways, exuding an infectious joy and inner strength. K.O.G’s electric vocals elevate the video’s energy, capturing the pride and inspiration drawn from Elsa Majimbo’s rise to fame. The video blends Afropop, Afrobeat, and soulful R&B elements, celebrating Aiza’s journey and the empowerment of loving boldly.
